{"id":121,"parent_id":114,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":121,"title":"Romans 8: \"Joint-Heirs with Christ\"","subtitle":"","short_title":"Romans 8: \"Joint-Heirs with Christ\"","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-8-joint-heirs-with-christ","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-8-joint-heirs-with-christ"},[".heading",{"id":"head8","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-8-joint-heirs-with-christ.head8"},["h1","Romans 8"],[".subtitle","“Joint-Heirs with Christ”"],[".intro","The promises found in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/8"},"Romans 8"],"are impressive and inspiring. Before reading these words of Paul, consider the following statement from the Prophet Joseph Smith: “[You] shall be heirs of God and joint heirs with Jesus Christ. What is it? To inherit the same power, the same glory and the same exaltation, until you arrive at the station of a God, and ascend the throne of eternal power, the same as those who have gone before” (Teachings of the Prophet Joseph Smith, 347)."]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",[".",{"id":"f17","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-8-joint-heirs-with-christ.f17"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-115-1.gif"}]],["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f18","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-8-joint-heirs-with-christ.f18"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/8"},"Romans 8"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Carnally minded, carnal mind"],"(vv. 6, 7)"],["td","Sinfully minded, having their minds set on n